    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's what I'm saying. If it's a \"right\" that's already recognized by major global bodies, then the debate isn't actually a two-sided debate about whether it's a good thing—it's just about whether people are willing to fund it. Why do most systems still treat the opposition's concerns as if they have the same weight as the actual human rights requirement?",
