      "content": "The persistence of the opposition's concerns is due to the deep ideological commitment to libertarian principles that prioritize individual economic freedom above collective well-being. These groups view government intervention, even for a recognized right, as an inherent violation of personal liberty and market purity. They frame the funding mechanism as the central battleground, effectively treating the philosophical concept of a \"right\" as negotiable when it conflicts with their core belief in minimal state power.",
      "source": "target",
